# Shell Script Standards

## General Requirements

- Use `set -euo pipefail` at the top of scripts
- Maintain backward compatibility when modifying existing scripts
- Test with both Podman (`podman compose`) and Docker (`docker compose`)
- Document any breaking changes in commit messages and relevant docs
- Follow the existing color-coded output convention (RED=errors, GREEN=success, YELLOW=warnings, BLUE=info)

## Key Scripts Reference

### Workspace Root

- `up.sh` -- Start RHDH with various configurations (modes, components, flags)
- `down.sh` -- Stop all containers, optionally remove volumes, always removes customization copies
- `backup.sh` -- Create portable backup archive of customizations and workspace files

### rhdh-customizations/

- `apply-customizations.sh` -- Copy customization files into `rhdh-local/` (run after every edit)
- `remove-customizations.sh` -- Remove customization copies from `rhdh-local/` (restore pristine state)

### rhdh-local/ (PRISTINE -- do not modify unless contributing upstream)

- `wait-for-plugins-and-start.sh` -- RHDH entrypoint: waits for plugins, merges config, starts Backstage
- `prepare-and-install-dynamic-plugins.sh` -- Plugin installer entrypoint: links config, runs install

### rhdh-local/developer-lightspeed/scripts/

- `start-lightspeed.sh` -- Interactive Lightspeed setup and startup
- `stop-lightspeed.sh` -- Stop Lightspeed containers

## When Modifying Scripts

- Update the script's header comment block to reflect changes
- If changing `up.sh` or `down.sh` flags, update `docs/scripts.md` and `docs/quick-reference.md`
- Ensure SELinux-safe bind mounts (`:Z` suffix) where needed
